cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the synthesis of controllers for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also leverages tools from generalization theory in machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control theory (cs.SY). The use of the PAC-Bayes framework further supports the possibility of it belonging to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the examples presented in the paper involve rich sensory inputs such as depth measurements, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
